snippet.title: Johnny Depp, Amber Heard apologise for illegally smuggling their dogs
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp, Amber Heard apologise for illegally smuggling their dogs 

Actor placed on a one-month good behaviour bond after pleading guilty to providing a false immigration document to immigration officials. The actor Amber Heard, who was prosecuted for illegally bringing her and husband Johnny Depp’s dogs into Australia, has emerged from the country’s highest profile criminal quarantine case with no conviction and a glowing character assessment by a magistrate.
